parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Parts for Cruise Control Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of parts for the cruise control recall can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to accidents or fires.
symptoms: Dealerships inform customers that parts are not available or will not be available for an extended period
customers are unable to schedule repair appointments
customers are told to continue driving the vehicle despite the potential safety risk.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake pad wear can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads wear out excessively fast
vibration or shuddering when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunction of the ABS braking system can cause the wheels to lock up, leading to loss of control, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: vibration or shuddering when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake system can cause loss of braking ability, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ejection of a spark plug can cause engine damage, loss of power, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: Spark plug blows out of the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake valve gasket can cause coolant to enter the cylinder, leading to engine damage, bent push rods, and potentially engine failure, which can result in accidents or strand the driver.
A malfunctioning cylinder head temperature sensor can cause the engine check light to illuminate, leading to false warnings and potentially causing the driver to ignore legitimate engine issues.
A cracked engine block can cause engine failure, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
Coolant leaks from the cylinder head can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially engine failure, which can result in accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: Coolant leaks from the cylinder head
external leaks from the thermostat housing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks into the engine block can cause engine failure, fires, and potentially accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: Fuel leaks into the engine block
fuel drips onto the engine torque.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fractured fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: rusted hole in the top of the fuel tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty filler hose can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: hose damage due to contact with the rear axle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The consumer hears a noise while driving
the vehicle pulls to one side
the tire tread separates from the rim
the tire falls off the rim
the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rim failure can cause the tire to fall off, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the vehicle becomes difficult to control
the consumer notices a noise or vibration while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate tire inspection can lead to undetected tire defects, which can cause tire failure, loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The consumer is not properly informed about tire defects
the tire inspector fails to detect tire defects
the consumer is misled about the condition of the tires.
